efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N)
space complexity: O(N)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution utilizes the `indexOf` method to find the first occurrence of the character `ch`. If found, it constructs a new string by reversing the substring from index 0 to the found index (inclusive) and concatenating it with the remaining part of the word. If `ch` is not found, the original word is returned. This approach has a time complexity of O(N) due to the potential traversal of the entire word string. The space complexity is also O(N) in the worst case, as a new string might be created with the same length as the input word. Energy implications are considered low as the operations involved are primarily string manipulation and do not involve computationally intensive tasks.

